docs.abstract: With the announcement of HomePod, a new home assistant, the company seems to be finally embracing the technologies it has long put on the back burner.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN JOSE, Calif. — One of Apple’s greatest strengths is timing. The company that’s hailed for innovation does not often invent things first — it didn’t create the first personal computer, the first digital music player or the first smartphone. Instead, Apple reinvents, slipping in and producing something more original than what we used to use.

headline.main: Apple Needs to Reinvent Itself. It Just Might Be Doing So.
